Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Senior Integration Developer position with MaintainX. I bring over three years of professional experience in integration solutions, REST API development, and full-stack systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade integration systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected an integration layer that translates natural-language intents into validated REST API calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, secure API integration, and data transformation across distributed systems. I built generative code solutions including API-aware templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows to accelerate integration with third-party systems, translating business requirements into technical solutions — directly mirroring the collaborative design work this role requires with Integration Consultants. To ensure reliability and performance, I built observability infrastructure using LangSmith and Langfuse for tracing, logging, and quality assurance to debug failures, track performance, and maintain technical documentation. I also implemented a concurrent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph with Node.js and TypeScript, enabling scalable execution across complex integration workflows. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handles file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO, creating technical specifications for integration with cloud and on-premise systems and ERP platforms — giving me direct experience with the multi-environment integration architecture this role demands. I also developed integration workflows using AWS Step Functions and Lambda for long-running data imports, implementing middleware patterns for reliable system integration and troubleshooting — both of which required the systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands. Together, these roles have prepared me to design, develop, and implement customized integration solutions and provide technical guidance to Integration Consultants, Integration Developers, and clients.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in technical communication and knowledge sharing — skills that translate directly into the collaborative culture and mentorship responsibilities this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using PyTorch and CUDA on an HPC cluster, managing the full model lifecycle from data preparation to deployment. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the technical guidance and support responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to MaintainX and its mission.

I have always been passionate about building software that keeps the physical world running and empowering frontline workers with enterprise-grade tools, and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering MaintainX's mission to make the life of blue-collar workers easier worldwide. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

